Forced photometry values for individual 30s exposures in orange (o)
and cyan (c) are provided in the long table. The measurements are
are in a flux unit, not magnitudes. But conversion is simple. 

The flux unit used is microJanskys, so AB mags are just

m_AB  = -2.5*log(Flux * 10^-6) + 8.9 

The error in m_AB can be calculated as above. Of course, will not be
meangingful when the significance is <3 sigma.
In those cases, the n-sigma upper limit (you can chose n) can be estimated from

m_AB (n-sigma upper limit) > -2.5*log(n * Flux_error * 10^-6) + 8.9

combined into a nightly mean. It is a weighted mean, with the points
weighted by the inverse variance. The number of 30s exposures which
were combined together is given in the last column. There are
small number of outliers, which you will see. You can ignore these
